 that great, as a mage I can assure you the ability to land something on a mob, despite uber resists, would RULE in many situations. Even though I am high levle and skilled, there are many places I cannot use pets, from my first planar raids I've had that problem, as have all mages. You know how FRUSTRATING it is casting 600hp nukes, that do around 150hp actual damage *consistantly* is ?<br>
Even at 60, Plane of Hate2..GAAAAAH! Can't use pets in most of it, and resist rates make me just wanna sit down play gems, it's truly horrible. Much of Plane of Air, Fear, epic mobs, a lot of dragons, TOV, the Hole we have problems in.<br>
<br>
But, we shouldn't get lures, that's wiz territory, rightfully. Wizards should always get low resist/unresistable/mob specific nukes.<br>
<br>
So the most &quot;in class&quot;, and fairest idea I can think of is this:<br>
<br>
Spell summons a solid projectile, that smashes into its target. Damage is  melee type, NOT spell resist, AC/dodge affect the damage. The projectile does 1/2 damage if an attack roll using 1hb skill fails, this should be easy to code, and prevents over power (caster has to &quot;guide projectile&quot; as it were, also atk buffs, rear positioning would help,  making it more fun and RP). Spell is conjuration, so is in character and mana efficient.<br>
For example:<br>
<br>
lvl 45 Stone Smash, a boulder literally drops onto the target's head. Damage is 400 hp.<br>
<br>
lvl 50 Blade Bolt, a bolt-type spell hurls a ballista bolt at the target, damage is 600 hp<br>
<br>
lvl 55 Blade Bolt 2, as Blade Bolt 1 but does 800hp<br>
<br>
Lvl 60 Meteor Blast, a meteor falls from the heavens on the target, damage is 1,000hp.<br>
<br>
 In your opinion as wizards. would these spells be in class for magicians, not step on wizard &quot;toes&quot; as it were, or be too powerful? I'm asking you guys because you are *the* nukers, and therefore I think need to be considered in such things <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Redorious<br>
Archmage<br>
karana <p><table width="95%" border="2">
