<br>
<br>
The problem is we OFTEN CANNOT USE PETS!!<br>
Where do we meet high resist mobs usually? On Raids, yes?<br>
<br>
Where can mages generally NOT use pets? RAIDS. Please do not tell me we can, because generally we CAN'T (I have used pets everywhere bar TOV and ST,  I know what I'm doing and I STILL can't or won't use pets in many raids).<br>
<br>
So imagine you are a mage doing a raid on hate or fear, your about level 50, going for planar armour maybe chance at epic drops. What does the mage do? Tries to nuke, notice, TRIES to. Until you hit 55 resists SUCK big time. You CANNOT use a pet, so that leaves you...hm maybe DS a tank, make some rods....<br>
<br>
How would YOU like it, as a wizard, if on a raid you are told &quot;Oh no nukes, O'Kiels the tanks, TL and port folk in and out.&quot; Would YOU be happy? That's the situation mages face, and I for one am rather *** about it.<br>
<br>
Oh and I am not getting at wizzies or trying to cut in on your action, which is why I am ASKING you <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I've said for ages wizzies need about a 40% increase in power, whether that's by mana regen, mana ratios etc is for you really to decide.<br>
<br>
mages, wizards and necros are the damage dealing Int casters, we've been screwed over for ages, I am merely proposing one way to help my class that's within reason. I don't mind the idea of mobs with high resists, I do object when we aren't given the means to affect them by using a different set of tools.<br>
<br>
I hear wizzies saying lures aren't good, well the mana ratios could sure be improved (why not a longer cast time but more normal mana/damage ratios?), but if you are having high resists would you STILL say they are crap?<br>
What I would like to point out is why is it wizards don't have MORE lures/banes from LOWER levels? As said up to lvl 55+ resists are a MAJOR pain in the butt, from 45+ when mages go on raids and can't use pets we are REALLY shafted.<br>
But also wizards frequently face  high level mobs from their LOWER levels whom they have trouble with resists on...<br>
So why isn't their gnoll bane spells around lvl 25? Low level lures from lvl20? I'm not talking uber nukes at those levels <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  At those kind of levels, mages/necros have pets, DS and life taps. Wizzies have..O'Kiels...to deal with high con high resist mobs. So why dont' you get banes/lures EARLIER ?<br>
<br>
<br>
Personally I think one of the big failings of EQ in regards to casters, is not so much equipment, but lack of variety and thought of spells. There should be far more mob dropped/quested spells at low level to give interest. For example you camp the magi in Guk for a SMR, but why doesn't he drop Froglocks Bane, lvl 40 spell, only affects froglocks, does say 600 hp, 6 sec cast, practically unresistable and low aggro. The spell is powerful, but only on *specific* mobs.<br>
<br>
I dont' know exactly what wizards need in terms of balancing, but isn't that, logical, useful and in character ? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I am trying to suggest a logical, useful and in character solution in regards to mage probelms, not trying to upset wizzies.<br>
<br>
<br>
Redorious<br>
Archmage<br>
