But how does one fix this without breaking them everywhere else. Granting mages lure type spells would make them much more viable in most raid encounters but it would totally unbalance them in many other situations. there needs to be some kind of fix but I am not sure that adding lures is the way to do it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>(Title left blank)</span><br>  Posts: 4842<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/17/02 10:12 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> No lures for you!</span><hr size=1> &quot;As it stands currently mages are seriously handicapped in any environment where they cannot use pets...&quot;<br>
